1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:06,049
By the same token, if we manage our thinking properly, if we think right toward people,

2
00:00:06,160 --> 00:00:10,529
we can find many qualities to like and admire in the same person.

3
00:00:11,040 --> 00:00:12,450
View it this way.

4
00:00:12,720 --> 00:00:15,970
Your mind is a mental broadcasting station.

5
00:00:16,240 --> 00:00:26,690
This broadcasting system transmits messages to you on two equally powerful channels, channel P, positive, and channel N, negative.

6
00:00:27,200 --> 00:00:30,370
Let's see how your broadcasting system works.

7
00:00:30,720 --> 00:00:39,169
Suppose that today your business superior, we'll call him Mr. Jacobs, called you into his office and reviewed your work with you.

8
00:00:39,600 --> 00:00:46,049
He complimented you on your work, but he also made some specific suggestions on how you can do it better.

9
00:00:46,320 --> 00:00:51,890
Tonight, it's only natural for you to recall the incident and do some thinking about it.

10
00:00:52,720 --> 00:00:57,330
If you tune in Channel N, the announcer will be saying something like this.

11
00:00:57,520 --> 00:00:58,370
Watch out!

12
00:00:58,560 --> 00:01:00,289
Jacobs is out to get you.

13
00:01:00,320 --> 00:01:01,490
He's a crab.

14
00:01:01,600 --> 00:01:04,610
You don't need any of his advice, to heck with it.

15
00:01:04,720 --> 00:01:07,409
Remember what Joe told you about Jacobs?

16
00:01:07,440 --> 00:01:08,370
He was right.

17
00:01:08,560 --> 00:01:11,890
Jacobs wants to grind you down like he did Joe.

18
00:01:12,000 --> 00:01:13,089
Resist him.

19
00:01:13,279 --> 00:01:15,970
Next time he calls you in, fight back.

20
00:01:16,160 --> 00:01:17,809
Better still, don't wait.

21
00:01:17,920 --> 00:01:22,529
Tomorrow, go in and ask him just what he really meant by his criticism.

22
00:01:23,279 --> 00:01:28,369
But tune in Channel P and the announcer will say something along these lines.

23
00:01:28,640 --> 00:01:31,890
You know, Mr. Jacobs is a pretty good fellow.

24
00:01:32,080 --> 00:01:35,410
Those suggestions he made to me seem pretty sound.

25
00:01:35,600 --> 00:01:41,970
If I put them to use, I can probably do a better job and position myself for an increase.

26
00:01:42,160 --> 00:01:44,130
The old boy did me a favor.

27
00:01:44,400 --> 00:01:48,210
Tomorrow I'll go in and thank him for his constructive help.

28
00:01:48,480 --> 00:01:49,569
Bill was right.

29
00:01:49,760 --> 00:01:52,369
Jacobs is a good man to work with.

30
00:01:53,600 --> 00:01:59,730
In this specific case, if you listen to Channel N, you're almost certain to make some bad,

31
00:01:59,760 --> 00:02:03,650
perhaps fatal mistake in your relations with your superior.

32
00:02:03,840 --> 00:02:13,650
But if you are tuned to Channel P, you are definitely certain to benefit from your superior's suggestions and at the same time draw yourself closer to him.

33
00:02:13,840 --> 00:02:15,730
He will appreciate that visit.

34
00:02:16,000 --> 00:02:17,250
Try it and see.

35
00:02:19,440 --> 00:02:25,250
Bear in mind that the longer you stay tuned to either Channel P or Channel N,

36
00:02:25,279 --> 00:02:29,650
the more interested you become and the harder it is to switch channels.

37
00:02:30,080 --> 00:02:37,650
This is true because one thought, positive or negative, sets off a whole chain reaction of similar thought.

38
00:02:38,000 --> 00:02:44,370
You may, for example, start off with such a simple minor negative thought as a person's accent,

39
00:02:44,480 --> 00:02:51,890
and find yourself soon thinking negatively about such unrelated topics as his political and religious beliefs,

40
00:02:51,920 --> 00:02:58,930
the car he drives, his personal habits, his relationship with his wife, even the way he combs his hair.

41
00:02:59,120 --> 00:03:03,410
And thinking this way surely won't get you where you want to go.

42
00:03:04,480 --> 00:03:08,529
You own it, so manage your thought broadcasting station.

43
00:03:08,640 --> 00:03:13,329
When your thoughts turn to people, make Channel P your listening habit.

